                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Table, found fragmented (the top broken into multiple fragments), but fully restored: legs (travertine) are solid slabs towards the rear, but the front profile carved to lion claw feet, with feathers to the top, and a volute profile.; table top (marble) has a raised moulding aroudn the edge, recessed upper surface, and a cornice profile to the sides. Legs are 65.5 cm tall, 11.3 cm wide, dimensions below are those of the table top slab itself.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</material>
